"_":484,"target":485},"ISic001359","http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001359",{"_":487,"target":488},"ISic001633","http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001633",{"type":490,"listBibl":491},"bibliography",[492,509],{"type":116,"bibl":493},[494,497,500,503,506],{"type":119,"n":120,"citedRange":121,"ptr":495,"ref":496},{"target":123},{"_":125,"target":125},{"author":129,"date":130,"citedRange":131,"ptr":498,"ref":499},{"target":133},{"_":135,"target":135},{"type":139,"n":140,"author":141,"title":140,"date":143,"citedRange":144,"ptr":501,"ref":502},{"target":146},{"_":148,"target":148},{"type":119,"n":151,"citedRange":152,"ptr":504,"ref":505},{"target":154},{"_":156,"target":156},{"author":160,"date":161,"citedRange":162,"ptr":507,"ref":508},{"target":164},{"_":166,"target":166},{"type":170,"bibl":50},[511],{"n":413,"url":93,"height":414,"width":415,"desc":94,"surfaceType":410},{"title":513,"body":514,"divs":515,"images":531},"ISic001626. Epitaph for Sokrates","  \u003Cdiv id=\"facsimile-images\">\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001626_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic001626_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001626.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic001626-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"edition\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div\">\u003Ca id=\"al1\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>ΣΩΚΡΑΤΗΣ\u003Cbr id=\"al2\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>christogramΠΑΝΤΩΝΟchristogram\u003Cbr id=\"al3\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>ΦΙΛΟΣΕΝΘΑ\u003Cbr id=\"al4\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>ΔΕΚΕΙΤΑΙ\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"apparatus\">\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>Text based on photograph\u003C/span>\u003C/span>; \u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"line 2\">line.2: \u003Cspan>Orsi, Agnello, Wessel: πάντων ὁ | φίλος; Ferrua, Korhonen: πάντων | φίλος (Ο is part of the Christogram)\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>Sokrates, the friend of all, lies here.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>Italian translation\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>Sokrates, l’amico di tutti, giace qui.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"commentary\">\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>This epitaph has a formula very similar to pagan epitaphs, although the presence of the two Christograms denotes it as Christian. Ferrua and Korhonen read \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">πάντων φίλος\u003C/span> with the interpretation of \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">Ο\u003C/span> as part of the Christogram, which in this case should be interpreted as \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">ὁ Χ(ριστό)ς\u003C/span> (the same hight of the letter \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">O\u003C/span> compared to the other letters of the text is probably a misinterpretation of the stonecutter). However, there is no need to eliminate the article since other parallels of similar epithets denoting friendship and affection in Christian inscriptions, such as IMusCatania 178 = \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001359\" target=\"_blank\">ISic001359\u003C/a> and SEG 65. 791 = \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001633\" target=\"_blank\">ISic001633\u003C/a> present the names of the deceased followed by adjectives preceded by the article (\u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">Κάλλιστος καὶ | Εὐκαρπία οἱ φιλόστορ|γοι\u003C/span> and \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">ὁ πανφίλ|ητος ... Εὐδέμων\u003C/span> respectively).\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"bibliography\">\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>  \u003Cli> 196 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003Cli> Agnello 1953 no.58) \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002211\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002211\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003Cli> Orsi NSA 1918 62 no.3 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001392\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001392\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003Cli> 1022 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000394\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000394\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003Cli> Ferrua 1989 110 no.416 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001995\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001995\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. \u003C/div>",[516,518,520,522,524,526,528],{"id":116,"html":517},"\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div\">\u003Ca id=\"al1\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>ΣΩΚΡΑΤΗΣ\u003Cbr id=\"al2\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>christogramΠΑΝΤΩΝΟchristogram\u003Cbr id=\"al3\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>ΦΙΛΟΣΕΝΘΑ\u003Cbr id=\"al4\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>ΔΕΚΕΙΤΑΙ\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>",{"id":452,"html":519},"\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>Text based on photograph\u003C/span>\u003C/span>; \u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"line 2\">line.2: \u003Cspan>Orsi, Agnello, Wessel: πάντων ὁ | φίλος; Ferrua, Korhonen: πάντων | φίλος (Ο is part of the Christogram)\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>",{"id":461,"html":521},"\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>Sokrates, the friend of all, lies here.\u003C/p>  ",{"id":461,"html":523},"\u003Ch2>Italian translation\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>Sokrates, l’amico di tutti, giace qui.\u003C/p>  ",{"id":466,"html":525},"\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>This epitaph has a formula very similar to pagan epitaphs, although the presence of the two Christograms denotes it as Christian. Ferrua and Korhonen read \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">πάντων φίλος\u003C/span> with the interpretation of \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">Ο\u003C/span> as part of the Christogram, which in this case should be interpreted as \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">ὁ Χ(ριστό)ς\u003C/span> (the same hight of the letter \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">O\u003C/span> compared to the other letters of the text is probably a misinterpretation of the stonecutter). However, there is no need to eliminate the article since other parallels of similar epithets denoting friendship and affection in Christian inscriptions, such as IMusCatania 178 = \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001359\" target=\"_blank\">ISic001359\u003C/a> and SEG 65. 791 = \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001633\" target=\"_blank\">ISic001633\u003C/a> present the names of the deceased followed by adjectives preceded by the article (\u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">Κάλλιστος καὶ | Εὐκαρπία οἱ φιλόστορ|γοι\u003C/span> and \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">ὁ πανφίλ|ητος ... Εὐδέμων\u003C/span> respectively).\u003C/p>  ",{"id":490,"html":527},"\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>  \u003Cli> 196 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003Cli> Agnello 1953 no.58) \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002211\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002211\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003Cli> Orsi NSA 1918 62 no.3 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001392\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001392\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003Cli> 1022 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000394\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000394\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003Cli> Ferrua 1989 110 no.416 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001995\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001995\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  ",{"id":529,"html":530},"license"," Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. ",[532,534],{"image":93,"thumb":533,"title":94},"ISic001626_tiled-thumb.tif",{"image":418,"thumb":535,"title":94},"ISic001626-thumb.jpg"],"uses":{"params":["slug"]}}]}
